  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, strip your <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666180367331-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666180367331-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666180367331-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666180367331-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666180367331-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>thyme leaves</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and reduce the heat to low</p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until the onion has caramelised and the sauce has become sticky</p><p>Once done, set aside to cool slightly – this is your<strong> red onion chutney</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooling will help to thicken the chutney!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666180370397-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666180370397-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666180370397-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666180370397-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666180370397-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for an initial 4-5 min or until the butternut squash cubes are fork-tender</p><p>Once tender, roughly mash the <strong>cooked butternut squash</strong> with a fork</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1666180374029-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1666180374029-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1666180374029-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1666180374029-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1666180374029-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> spinach</strong> to the bowl with the mashed butternut squash and return it to the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1-2 min further or until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Once wilted, add your <strong>goats cheese </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>goats cheese, spinach & butternut squash filling</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1666180377657-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1666180377657-x400.jpg",
