          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1666180384104-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush a little <strong>cold water </strong>around the edges of the pastry</p><p>Fold the <strong>pastry</strong> over the filling and seal firmly together, then use a fork to crimp along the edge</p><p>Brush the pastry with <strong>milk</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining thyme leaves</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the pastry is puffed up, golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>goats cheese, spinach & red onion butternut squash rolls</strong></p>",
